1.Create User , group , add user to group , sudoer file , remove group and user
Create user : sudo adduser username
Login into user :- su - username
Check if user is created or not - grep username /etc/passwd
cd /etc/
ls passwd
sudo cat passwd
Adding user to sudoers file : sudo usermod -aG sudo username
Adding user to a group - sudo usermod -aG groupname username
Checking if user is present or not in the group - grep username /etc/group
Checking user if present in group or not - groups username
Group
Create a user group : - sudo groupadd groupname
Remove from the group : sudo gpasswd -d username groupname
Delete user :sudo userdel username | sudo userdel -r username
Delete group: sudo groupdel groupname
2.htop
sha1sum /dev/zero &
3.Kill command: kill pid
Kill -9 pid ( sigkill) to delete the resource immediately / forcefully
4.Unzip a file : 1. First Install unzip sudo apt-get install unzip
unzip filename.zip
unzip example.zip -d /path/to/destination
Unzip example.zip 1file.txt 2file.txt


